B.  Well, it was easy.  I just ignored it.  Back then  the server was young and I didnt realize the impact of the AC loss.  Once I realized it, my first consideration was weight in everything I did.  I sacrificed lots of AC at the lower levels to stay underweight.  It isn't easy, but you learn to appreciate 12AC items that only weigh .2, and you also see why Monks so fervently seek Vox/Naggy bags  (On that, if anyone has a Vox bag for Trade, I will trade you my Tinkerer's bag, plus a few other things) <p>Logoth Shadar<br>Grandmaster<br>Guild Captain of Clachan Brigh, Bristlebane Server<br>BUFF THE LOG!!!</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#a8a8a8><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub8.ezboard.com/udranwyr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dranwyr</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Codemonkey</span><br> <font color=#238e23>(8/26/01 12:49:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need your help</span><hr size=1> Aaz, my monk is only at 8 pounds, or 6 pounds when not holding knuckledusters.  Cured Silk is better than raw silk in AC and in weight:  it's 0.1 per piece.  jewelry itself is typically 0.1, the heaviest earring I know of is the orcfang, and that's 0.5 I think.  In any case, you can always send a tell to my monkette.  (Rash of em going around?  I think not... Bronwyn is older than Logoth, though she owes much of her gear to him)  Feel free to pester for monk ideas and gear when she is on, as that is my best time to be able to check the gear.<br>
